{"id":1661099,"retrievedAt":"2026-04-01T12:12:24.853Z","response":{"adult":false,"backdrop_path":"/nfVztG0XBsjwSL5kR5GDWY2BVHg.jpg","belongs_to_collection":null,"budget":0,"genres":[{"id":10402,"name":"Music"}],"homepage":"","id":1661099,"imdb_id":null,"origin_country":["GB"],"original_language":"en","original_title":"Mike Oldfield: Tubular Bells","overview":"Tubular Bells is the debut studio album by the English musician Mike Oldfield, released on 25 May 1973 as the first album on Virgin Records. It comprises two mostly instrumental tracks. Oldfield, who was 19 years old when it was recorded, played almost all the instruments.  Tubular Bells initially sold slowly, but gained worldwide attention in December 1973 when its opening theme was used for the soundtrack to the horror film The Exorcist. This led to a surge in sales which increased Oldfield's profile and played an important part in the growth of the Virgin Group. It stayed in the top ten of the UK Albums Chart for one year from March 1974, during which it reached number one for one week. It reached number three on the US Billboard 200, and number one in Canada and Australia. It has sold more than 2.7 million copies in the UK, and an estimated 15 million copies worldwide.","popularity":0,"poster_path":"/bQsAaRQgyIP0p73CrERuqZ7XykV.jpg","production_companies":[],"production_countries":[],"release_date":"1973-05-25","revenue":0,"runtime":49,"spoken_languages":[],"status":"Released","tagline":"","title":"Mike Oldfield: Tubular Bells","video":false,"vote_average":0,"vote_count":0,"alternative_titles":{"titles":[]},"credits":{"cast":[{"adult":false,"gender":2,"id":8968,"known_for_department":"Sound","name":"Mike Oldfield","original_name":"Mike Oldfield","popularity":0.6189,"profile_path":"/zXG5jeZDEIW6o1cInUiLqklHlUX.jpg","cast_id":1,"character":"","credit_id":"69cbbbbaa23e4f58d2abbc33","order":0}],"crew":[{"adult":false,"gender":2,"id":8968,"known_for_department":"Sound","name":"Mike Oldfield","original_name":"Mik